and Seifert 2003
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Notes:</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<bibRefCitation author="Csosz, S" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="211 - 223" title="Poneratestacea Emery, 1895 stat. nov. - A sister species of P. coarctata (Latreille, 1802) (Hymenoptera: Formicidae)." volume="49" year="2003">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Csősz">Csosz</normalizedToken>
and Seifert (2003)
</bibRefCitation>
revived the name 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera coarctata var. testacea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="coarctata" variety="testacea">Ponera coarctata var. testacea</taxonomicName>
from synonymy and raised it to species. 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera testacea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="testacea">Ponera testacea</taxonomicName>
is a more thermophilous species than 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera coarctata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coarctata">Ponera coarctata</taxonomicName>
and seems to be widely distributed in Southern Europe. We are pretty sure that many of the previous records of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera coarctata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coarctata">Ponera coarctata</taxonomicName>
for Bulgaria might belong to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera testacea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="testacea">Ponera testacea</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
